        "title_part_one": "Switching to IEMs should feel right",
        "title_part_two": "from the first Sunday",
        "title_accent_color": "primary-500",
        "body": "<p>One of the biggest reasons worship musicians put off switching to IEMs is simple: they worry it will feel wrong on stage, or that they will spend the whole service readjusting.</p><p>Wave is designed to sit securely from the moment you put it in. The over-ear hook locks it in place - no fiddling, no falling out, no distraction.</p><p>Once the fit clicks, everything changes. You can hear your own instrument clearly, stay in the mix, and actually focus on leading worship instead of fighting your gear.</p>"
